'''Political egalitarianism''' is where members of a society are of equal standing in terms of political power or influence.<ref> https://plato.stanford.edu/entries/egalitarianism/ </ref> It is a founding principle of various forms of [[democracy]]. It was an idea which was supported by Thomas Jefferson.
It is a concept similar to [[moral reciprocity]] and [[legal equality]].
